      }
    ],
    "Description": "### Impact\nThe HAProxy PROXY protocol v2 codec in netty leaks native or heap memory on every connection when a client sends a syntactically valid header containing nested `PP2_TYPE_SSL` TLVs (type-length-value records) at depth two or greater. The leak occurs on the successful parse path — no exception is thrown, the message fires downstream, the decoder removes itself, and the application releases the `HAProxyMessage` normally. Yet the underlying cumulation buffer (a pooled, potentially direct `ByteBuf` allocated by the channel) remains permanently pinned.",
    "Origin": "UNSPECIFIED",
    "PublishedAt": "2026-06-11T20:19:27Z",
    "Severity": "HIGH",
    "Summary": "Netty HAProxy: Unbalanced Reference Count in Nested PP2_TYPE_SSL TLV Parsing Leads to Memory Exhaustion",
    "UpdatedAt": "2026-07-21T12:33:32Z",
